        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 6:52AM MDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 651 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lemmon, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Thunder Hawk around 700 AM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
